<div class="p text-right font-secondary"><a href="table/T1/" class="usa-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Open in a new tab</a></div></section></section></section><section id="S25"><h2 class="pmc_sec_title">5 Results</h2>
<p id="P42">We ran Maitreya on the eight clinical procedures prediction tasks datasets in Table 1, in order to answer the research questions in section 4.2. <a href="#T2" class="usa-link">Table 2</a>, <a href="#T3" class="usa-link">3</a> and <a href="#T4" class="usa-link">4</a> present the results of the procedures prediction with the three feature selection strategies. All the tables have the same structure of contents. Symbols (first column) refers to the use of no temporal analysis as features, thus, the symbols are the types of events in the data, and the next columns are of the TIRPs with three types of representations: Boolean, Horizontal Support and Mean Duration. The results are presented as means and 95% confidence intervals. The baseline methods: symbols and Boolean TIRPs are based on (<a href="#R2" class="usa-link" aria-describedby="R2">Batal et al, 2012</a>).</p>
